{
  "info": {
    "name": "Multi Tenant RAG API",
    "description": "Postman collection for the Multi Tenant RAG API\n\n## Getting Started\n1. Set `baseUrl` variable to your server (default: `http://localhost:4000/api/v1`)\n2. Run **Auth > Login User** or **Auth > Login Admin** to get tokens\n3. Tokens are auto-stored via the Tests scripts — subsequent requests use them\n\n## Auth Flow\n- **JWT Access Token** is set as `accessToken` collection variable\n- **JWT Refresh Token** is set as `refreshToken` collection variable\n- Use **Auth > Refresh** to renew before expiry (15 min default)\n- Use **Auth > Logout** to invalidate refresh tokens\n\n## Common Headers\n| Header | Value | Required For |\n|--------|-------|-------------|\n| `Authorization` | `Bearer {{accessToken}}` | All authenticated routes |\n| `x-company-id` | `<company-uuid>` | Company-scoped routes (documents, users) |\n| `X-Requested-With` | `XMLHttpRequest` | All non-GET authenticated routes (CSRF) |",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "baseUrl": "{{baseUrl}}"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "baseUrl",
      "value": "http://localhost:4000/api/v1",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "accessToken",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "refreshToken",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "companyId",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "documentId",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "storageKey",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "userId",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
